# Movie Finder — Cursor Rules

You are working in the Movie Finder monorepo root.
Primary reference: CLAUDE.md (loaded automatically by Claude Code, also valid for Cursor).

## Architecture summary

- `backend/` — FastAPI + LangGraph pipeline (Python 3.13, uv workspace)
- `frontend/` — Angular 21 SPA (TypeScript 5.9)
- `docs/` — MkDocs site + PlantUML diagrams + Structurizr C4 + ADRs
- `infrastructure/` — Terraform IaC (Azure primary)
- `mcp/` — Internal MCP servers (qdrant-explorer is the only implemented one)

## Development contract

All quality commands run inside Docker — never on the host.

```
make up              # start the full stack
make down            # stop all containers
make mkdocs          # docs site → http://localhost:8001
make structurizr     # C4 diagrams → http://localhost:18080
```

## Cross-cutting rules

- Python: mypy --strict, ruff (100 chars), no bare except, no print(), async all the way
- TypeScript: no any, standalone components, signals not BehaviorSubject, strict mode
- No secrets in code — detect-secrets pre-commit hook enforces this
- Conventional Commits: type(scope): summary
- Tests are required on every PR

## CI/CD

Per-repo pipelines: Lint + Test only (no image build).
Root pipeline (Jenkins + GitHub Actions): Build images → Deploy staging → Production gate.

## What NOT to do

- Never `git add -A` — submodule state and secrets can be staged accidentally
- Never `--no-verify` pre-commit
- Never push directly to main
- Never instantiate shared resources inside route handlers — use FastAPI `Depends()`
- Never add `if provider == "openai":` branching — use the Strategy pattern
